00:17.514 --> 00:18.514
Good morning.

00:18.515 --> 00:19.681
Good morning.

00:19.683 --> 00:21.750
You the one that called us?
Yes, officers.

00:21.752 --> 00:23.952
I came to open up the bank
this morning,

00:23.954 --> 00:25.187
and I found this...

00:25.189 --> 00:27.756
person...
sleeping by the ATMs.

00:27.758 --> 00:29.457
Now, I don't know if he's drunk,

00:29.459 --> 00:31.693
but he is passed out
and he smells.

00:31.695 --> 00:32.894
Ugh.

00:32.896 --> 00:34.096
He's disturbing our customers,

00:34.097 --> 00:35.864
so can you please
get rid of him?

00:35.866 --> 00:36.866
Yeah. You got it.

00:36.867 --> 00:38.033
Yeah, we got it.
Thank you.

00:38.035 --> 00:40.602
Did you ever think
it'd be this glamorous?

00:40.604 --> 00:43.038
All right!

00:43.040 --> 00:44.306
Time to check out.

00:44.308 --> 00:46.041
That's right.
Rise and shine.

00:46.043 --> 00:47.275
(sighs)

00:47.277 --> 00:48.277
Come on.

00:48.278 --> 00:49.845
Let's go, let's go.

00:53.617 --> 00:55.217
You okay?

00:57.421 --> 00:59.061
How old are you, bud?
Wh-What's your name?

01:00.591 --> 01:01.857
How'd you end up here?

01:03.560 --> 01:05.327
Is there someone
that we can call?

01:05.328 --> 01:07.329
You can talk to us.

01:07.331 --> 01:08.396
You're not in any trouble.

01:08.398 --> 01:09.664
Officers, please.

01:09.666 --> 01:11.366
Yeah.

01:14.371 --> 01:16.872
Why don't we get him
back to the precinct.

01:16.874 --> 01:18.940
All right. Sounds good.
Call ACS.

01:19.810 --> 01:21.576
Hey! Hey!

01:25.616 --> 01:26.715
Hey!
Hey, move!

01:26.717 --> 01:27.749
Move!

01:27.751 --> 01:29.651
Stop! Hey!

01:29.653 --> 01:30.952
(horn blaring)
Whoa!

01:30.954 --> 01:32.721
What are you doing, huh?
Why you running?

01:32.723 --> 01:34.823
(grunting)
Why you running, huh?

01:34.825 --> 01:36.892
Can't be seen with no cops.

01:36.894 --> 01:38.260
Yeah? Well, why?

01:38.262 --> 01:40.362
What are you afraid of?

01:41.265 --> 01:43.899
All right. Come on.

01:43.901 --> 01:45.200
Let's go.

01:48.472 --> 01:49.804
Put any weight on it?

01:49.806 --> 01:51.740
Not without moaning.

01:51.742 --> 01:53.642
I told him to be careful
of the black ice.

01:53.644 --> 01:54.910
You can't see it.

01:54.912 --> 01:56.878
Well, how in the hell
can you be careful of something

01:56.880 --> 01:58.046
you can't see?

01:58.048 --> 01:59.881
I think it's
just a sprain,

01:59.883 --> 02:02.284
but the swelling has to go down
before we can even do an MRI,

02:02.286 --> 02:04.753
so you-you have to keep it
iced and elevated.

02:04.755 --> 02:06.021
Well, I got to get to work.

02:06.023 --> 02:07.389
You'll have to do it
from here, Frank.

02:07.391 --> 02:09.124
I'm sorry.
HENRY: Francis.

02:09.126 --> 02:10.758
From when I had my hip surgery.

02:10.761 --> 02:13.728
Gee, thanks.

02:13.730 --> 02:21.372
Little time off won't kill you.
Now, I'll check in with you later..

02:21.374 --> 02:24.142
Last time, they had to shoot me.

02:27.380 --> 02:28.946
(knocking)

02:28.948 --> 02:30.815
Mm, Evan Beck.

02:30.817 --> 02:32.116
I thought I smelled you coming.

02:32.118 --> 02:33.785
I hope you didn't wear
all that cologne just for me.

02:33.787 --> 02:35.253
No.

02:35.255 --> 02:38.055
But, uh, I do come
bearing gifts.

02:38.057 --> 02:39.824
Listen, I'm, uh,

02:39.826 --> 02:41.492
ready to deal
on Thomas Kowalski,

02:41.494 --> 02:43.294
save us both
a lot of aggravation.

02:43.296 --> 02:44.595
I'm listening.

02:44.597 --> 02:46.497
He's willing to
plead to possession.

02:46.499 --> 02:49.100
It's a first offense, so
how does, uh, six months in jail

02:49.102 --> 02:50.501
and court-mandated rehab sound?

02:50.503 --> 02:52.904
Generous, but I'm not pleading
this one out.

02:52.906 --> 02:54.705
You're going for intent to sell?

02:54.707 --> 02:56.207
Come on, Erin,

02:56.209 --> 02:57.842
all the guy did was run
a red light, and we both know

02:57.844 --> 02:58.943
the amounts were
on the borderline.

02:58.945 --> 03:00.244
Okay, that's not all he did.

03:00.246 --> 03:02.280
He was intoxicated and
belligerent with the officers.

03:02.282 --> 03:03.548
That's why he was arrested,

03:03.550 --> 03:05.316
and then they found the drugs
in the car.

03:05.318 --> 03:07.018
Yeah, you're just being
a hard-ass

03:07.020 --> 03:09.187
because Thomas is a guard
at Rikers Island

03:09.189 --> 03:11.122
and it's gonna be
a whole scandal in the press

03:11.124 --> 03:12.256
and you love that.

03:12.258 --> 03:14.125
I love beating you, Evan.

03:14.127 --> 03:16.761
This really is about me,
isn't it?

03:16.763 --> 03:18.863
You're still mad
about our last case?

03:18.865 --> 03:21.265
I won. Why would I be mad?
Because I accused you

03:21.267 --> 03:22.900
of withholding evidence
and dragged your name

03:22.902 --> 03:24.836
through the mud. Yeah,
I'm just gonna speak to McCoy,

03:24.838 --> 03:26.270
try to get another prosecutor
assigned.

03:26.272 --> 03:27.672
Happy hunting,

03:27.674 --> 03:29.874
but I'll be seeing you in court.
And why don't you tell

03:29.876 --> 03:31.409
your client
to bring his toothbrush.

03:31.411 --> 03:33.277
He's gonna be going away
for about a decade.

03:33.279 --> 03:35.480
Well, we'll see about that.

03:41.287 --> 03:43.988
JAMIE: Children's Services is
gonna get you some housing,

03:43.990 --> 03:47.124
but it's gonna take at least
a few more hours, so...

03:47.126 --> 03:49.260
why don't you tell us
what's going on.

03:49.262 --> 03:51.128
We can't help if
we don't know.

03:51.130 --> 03:52.697
You want to help me?

03:52.699 --> 03:55.633
Go get me a sandwich.
I'm a growing boy.

03:57.270 --> 03:58.903
We got candy and
chips in the machine.

03:58.905 --> 04:00.471
Those are your choices.

04:00.473 --> 04:03.174
Get me a chocolate bar then.

04:03.977 --> 04:05.877
I'll go.

04:05.879 --> 04:07.979
You're real sweet.

04:12.785 --> 04:14.752
Where you from, TJ?

04:14.754 --> 04:17.387
Baltimore. Moved here
a couple weeks ago.

04:17.390 --> 04:18.390
Why'd you move?

04:18.391 --> 04:20.291
Mom got locked up.

04:20.293 --> 04:21.192
For what?

04:21.194 --> 04:22.693
Drugs.

04:22.695 --> 04:25.363
Sent me on the bus
to my Aunt Christy,

04:25.365 --> 04:27.365
gave her money
to take care of me.

04:27.367 --> 04:29.734
Christy? What's her full name?

04:29.736 --> 04:31.502
Christy Stewart.

04:31.504 --> 04:32.737
Where'd you two stay?

04:32.739 --> 04:34.338
The city.

04:34.340 --> 04:37.275
She has a cart we fill
with bottles and cans.

04:37.277 --> 04:39.577
We recycle them.

04:39.579 --> 04:41.479
That's our hustle.

04:41.481 --> 04:45.249
So what happened? How'd you
wind up at that bank alone?

04:45.251 --> 04:47.418
JANKO:
Whatever it is,

04:47.420 --> 04:50.021
we'll protect you.

04:50.857 --> 04:52.590
That'd be a first.

04:52.592 --> 04:55.726
Try us.

04:55.728 --> 04:57.795
(scoffs)

04:59.566 --> 05:03.401
Two nights ago,
my aunt disappeared.

05:03.403 --> 05:07.305
I think her boyfriend--
this dude they call Ghost--

05:07.307 --> 05:09.173
killed her.

05:10.710 --> 05:13.277
Is that who you're afraid of?

05:15.548 --> 05:18.215
Why do you think he killed her?
Did you see him do it?

05:19.285 --> 05:21.052
You actually see her body?

05:21.054 --> 05:23.421
No. I found her cart.

05:23.423 --> 05:26.490
It was... crashed out in a lot.

05:26.492 --> 05:29.660
All her stuff was on the ground.

05:31.898 --> 05:33.764
I found this.

05:39.739 --> 05:43.274
Christy would never leave me
out on the street.

05:45.645 --> 05:48.245
I know she got killed.

